<sect1 id="EXP">
  <!-- DNT-Start --><title>EXP<indexterm>
      <primary>EXP</primary>
    </indexterm></title><!-- DNT-End -->

  <para><emphasis role="bold"><!-- DNT-Start -->EXP<!-- DNT-End --><indexterm>
      <primary><!-- DNT-Start -->EXP<!-- DNT-End --> function</primary>
    </indexterm>(</emphasis><emphasis>n</emphasis><emphasis
  role="bold">)</emphasis></para>

  <para><informaltable colsep="1" frame="all" rowsep="1">
      <tgroup cols="2">
        <colspec colwidth="79.50pt" />

        <colspec colwidth="309.30pt" />

        <tbody>
          <row>
            <entry><!-- DNT-Start -->n<!-- DNT-End --></entry>

            <entry>The real number to evaluate.</entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry><!-- DNT-Start -->Return:<!-- DNT-End --></entry>

            <entry><!-- DNT-Start -->EXP<!-- DNT-End --> returns a single real value.</entry>
          </row>
        </tbody>
      </tgroup>
    </informaltable></para>

  <para>The <emphasis role="bold"><!-- DNT-Start -->EXP<!-- DNT-End --> </emphasis>function returns the natural
  exponential value of the parameter (en). This is the opposite of the <!-- DNT-Start -->LN<!-- DNT-End -->
  function<indexterm>
      <primary><!-- DNT-Start -->LN<!-- DNT-End --> function</primary>
    </indexterm>.</para>

  <para>Example:</para>

  <!-- DNT-Start --><programlisting>MyPI := EXP(3.14159);
Interim := ROUND(1000 * (EXP(MyPI)/(1 + EXP(MyPI))));</programlisting><!-- DNT-End -->

  <para>See Also: <link linkend="LN"><!-- DNT-Start -->LN<!-- DNT-End --></link>, <link linkend="SQRT"><!-- DNT-Start -->SQRT<!-- DNT-End --></link>, <link linkend="POWER"><!-- DNT-Start -->POWER<!-- DNT-End --></link></para>
</sect1>
